#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:139
msgid ""
"You consolidate localization review notes. You receive PRIOR_STATE (notes "
"carried from earlier batches) and NEW_FINDINGS (observations for the current"
" batch only). Produce UPDATED_STATE: a concise bullet list (max ~800 words) "
"that (1) keeps recurring issues, terminology gaps, and locale patterns from "
"PRIOR_STATE if still relevant, (2) adds important new points from "
"NEW_FINDINGS, (3) drops noise. Stay within the facts given; do not invent "
"msgids. Use the same language as specified in the user message."
msgstr ""
"You consolidate localization review notes. You receive PRIOR_STATE (notes "
"carried from earlier batches) and NEW_FINDINGS (observations for the current"
" batch only). Produce UPDATED_STATE: a concise bullet list (max ~800 words) "
"that (1) keeps recurring issues, terminology gaps, and locale patterns from "
"PRIOR_STATE if still relevant, (2) adds important new points from "
"NEW_FINDINGS, (3) drops noise. Stay within the facts given; do not invent "
"msgids. Use the same language as specified in the user message."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:149
msgid "Response language for UPDATED_STATE: {lang}"
msgstr "Response language for UPDATED_STATE: {lang}"

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:150
msgid "Batch progress: {i} / {total}."
msgstr "Batch progress: {i} / {total}."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:151
msgid "(none — first batch)"
msgstr "(none — first batch)"

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:152
msgid "(no findings)"
msgstr "(no findings)"

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:154
msgid ""
"Output ONLY the bullet list for UPDATED_STATE, with a short "
"\"CarryForward:\" line at the end listing msgid/locale pairs to watch in "
"later batches (or \"none\")."
msgstr ""
"Output ONLY the bullet list for UPDATED_STATE, with a short "
"\"CarryForward:\" line at the end listing msgid/locale pairs to watch in "
"later batches (or \"none\")."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:164
msgid "Rolling merge returned empty; using local merge fallback."
msgstr "Rolling merge returned empty; using local merge fallback."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:171
msgid "Rolling merge failed ({err}); using local merge fallback."
msgstr "Rolling merge failed ({err}); using local merge fallback."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:186
msgid "You are reviewing a slice of a translation catalog. Reply in {lang}."
msgstr "You are reviewing a slice of a translation catalog. Reply in {lang}."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:191
msgid "(No prior notes — this is the first batch.)"
msgstr "(No prior notes — this is the first batch.)"

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:193
msgid "New data for this batch only:"
msgstr "New data for this batch only:"

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:196
msgid ""
"Rules: (1) Comment only on rows in this batch. (2) Reference msgid and "
"locale. (3) Flag likely copy-paste of default locale, broken placeholders, "
"or obvious untranslated fragments when the locale suggests translation. (4) "
"Note cross-batch themes only if they match ROLLING_NOTES or clearly repeat "
"here."
msgstr ""
"Rules: (1) Comment only on rows in this batch. (2) Reference msgid and "
"locale. (3) Flag likely copy-paste of default locale, broken placeholders, "
"or obvious untranslated fragments when the locale suggests translation. (4) "
"Note cross-batch themes only if they match ROLLING_NOTES or clearly repeat "
"here."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:213
msgid "Write the final localization review report in {lang}."
msgstr "Write the final localization review report in {lang}."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:216
msgid "Number of catalog batches reviewed: {n}."
msgstr "Number of catalog batches reviewed: {n}."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:219
msgid ""
"Produce: (1) Executive summary, (2) Top issues by severity, (3) Locale-"
"specific gaps if any, (4) Suggested next checks. Be concise; do not invent "
"msgids not implied by the notes."
msgstr ""
"Produce: (1) Executive summary, (2) Top issues by severity, (3) Locale-"
"specific gaps if any, (4) Suggested next checks. Be concise; do not invent "
"msgids not implied by the notes."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:248
msgid "No catalog data to send (empty project or batches)."
msgstr "No catalog data to send (empty project or batches)."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:256
msgid ""
"You are an expert software localization reviewer. Data lines are MSGID, "
"LOCALE, TEXT separated by tabs. A header line may show default_locale=. You "
"are given ROLLING_NOTES from earlier batches to track trends—do not "
"contradict them without evidence in the current batch."
msgstr ""
"You are an expert software localization reviewer. Data lines are MSGID, "
"LOCALE, TEXT separated by tabs. A header line may show default_locale=. You "
"are given ROLLING_NOTES from earlier batches to track trends—do not "
"contradict them without evidence in the current batch."

#: i18n/llm_catalog_review.py:262
msgid ""
"You write clear localization audit reports for developers. Only use "
"information in ACCUMULATED_NOTES; do not fabricate msgids."
msgstr ""
"You write clear localization audit reports for developers. Only use "
"information in ACCUMULATED_NOTES; do not fabricate msgids."

